query: User Rank and Hoarded Rep.
schema: CREATE TABLE Users (Id number, Reputation number, CreationDate time, DisplayName text, LastAccessDate time, WebsiteUrl text, Location text, AboutMe text, Views number, UpVotes number, DownVotes number, ProfileImageUrl text, EmailHash text, AccountId number)
sql: SELECT p.Id AS "user_link", p.Ranking, SUBSTRING(CAST(CAST(Ranking AS FLOAT) / Count * 100.00 AS TEXT), 1, 6) + '%' AS Percentile, Reputation, SUBSTRING(CAST(CAST(Reputation AS FLOAT) / Sum * 100.00 AS TEXT), 1, 6) + '%' AS "Hoarded rep" FROM (SELECT Id, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY Reputation DESC) AS Ranking, Reputation FROM df WHERE Reputation > @MinRep) AS p, (SELECT Count = COUNT(*) FROM df WHERE Reputation > @MinRep) AS Counts, (SELECT Sum = SUM(Reputation) FROM df WHERE Reputation > @MinRep) AS Rep ORDER BY ranking LIMIT 1000

query: the average elevation translated from feet to meters of all large airports in the US grouped by state and sorted by elevation

query: the average elevation all large airports in the US grouped and sorted by state

query: Find coincident activity between two users.
schema: CREATE TABLE Posts (    Id number,    PostTypeId number,    AcceptedAnswerId number,    ParentId number,    CreationDate time,    DeletionDate time,    Score number,    ViewCount number,    Body text,    OwnerUserId number,    OwnerDisplayName text,    LastEditorUserId number,    LastEditorDisplayName text,    LastEditDate time,    LastActivityDate time,    Title text,    Tags text,    AnswerCount number,    CommentCount number,    FavoriteCount number,    ClosedDate time,    CommunityOwnedDate time,    ContentLicense text)
sql: WITH Interesting(UserId) AS (SELECT 342852 UNION ALL SELECT 57611) SELECT PostId = df.Id, QuestionId = COALESCE(a.Id, df.Id), AnswerId = CASE WHEN df.PostTypeId = 2 THEN df.Id ELSE NULL END FROM df AS df LEFT JOIN df AS a ON df.PostTypeId = 2 AND df.ParentId = a.Id WHERE EXISTS(SELECT * FROM Interesting AS i WHERE df.OwnerUserId = i.UserId) OR EXISTS(SELECT * FROM Interesting AS i WHERE a.OwnerUserId = i.UserId)

query: the aggreagated count of each type of airport in the US grouped and sorted by state one row per state with each type in its own column
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'heliport' THEN 1 END) AS heliport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'seaplane_base' THEN 1 END) AS seaplane_base_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'balloonport' THEN 1 END) AS balloonport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'closed' THEN 1 END) AS closed_count 
FROM df 
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state with a colunm for each airport type and a column with an array of all large airport iata codes with names sorted by state
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region AS state, 
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS large_airport_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS medium_airport_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS small_airport_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'seaplane_base' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS seaplane_base_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'heliport' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS heliport_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN type = 'balloonport' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS balloonport_count,
ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN CONCAT(iata_code, ': ', name) ELSE NULL END) FILTER (WHERE type = 'large_airport') AS large_airports
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

query:
Find questions titles that are not phrased as questions. Find question titles that do not contain the Five Ws (Who, What, When, Where and why), interrogative words, and question marks.

This query MAY be useful for identifying titles that aren't phrased as a question or low quality questions.

Special thanks: s.tk/users/398665
schema: CREATE TABLE df (Id number, PostTypeId number, AcceptedAnswerId number, ParentId number, CreationDate time, DeletionDate time, Score number, ViewCount number, Body text, OwnerUserId number, OwnerDisplayName text, LastEditorUserId number, LastEditorDisplayName text, LastEditDate time, LastActivityDate time, Title text, Tags text, AnswerCount number, CommentCount number, FavoriteCount number, ClosedDate time, CommunityOwnedDate time, ContentLicense text)

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state with a colunm for each airport type and a column with an array of iata codes and names
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport,
       ARRAY_AGG(JSONB_BUILD_OBJECT('iata_code', iata_code, 'name', name)) AS airport_info
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region

query: Average score per hundred views.
schema: CREATE TABLE Posts (Id number, PostTypeId number, AcceptedAnswerId number, ParentId number, CreationDate time, DeletionDate time, Score number, ViewCount number, Body text, OwnerUserId number, OwnerDisplayName text, LastEditorUserId number, LastEditorDisplayName text, LastEditDate time, LastActivityDate time, Title text, Tags text, AnswerCount number, CommentCount number, FavoriteCount number, ClosedDate time, CommunityOwnedDate time, ContentLicense text)
sql: WITH counts_cte AS (SELECT LAST_DATE_OF_MONTH(p.CreationDate) AS Cmonth, SUM(Score) AS Score, SUM(ViewCount) AS Views FROM df AS p WHERE PostTypeId = 1 GROUP BY LAST_DATE_OF_MONTH(p.CreationDate)) SELECT Cmonth, 100 * (CAST(Score AS FLOAT)) / (CAST(Views AS FLOAT)) AS "score_per_view" FROM counts_cte ORDER BY Cmonth

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state sorted by large_airport_count with a colunm for each airport type and a column with an array of all large airport iata codes
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport_count, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport_count, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport_count, 
       ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN iata_code END) AS large_airport_iata_codes 
FROM df 
WHERE iso_country = 'US' 
GROUP BY iso_region 
ORDER BY large_airport_count DESC

query: Fast-gun' distribution for a user.
schema: CREATE TABLE df (Id number, SuggestedEditId number, UserId number, VoteTypeId number, CreationDate time, TargetUserId number, TargetRepChange number)
sql: WITH Dates AS (SELECT a.Id, q.CreationDate AS QDate, a.CreationDate AS ADate FROM df AS q, df AS a WHERE q.Id = a.ParentId AND q.PostTypeId = 1 AND a.PostTypeId = 2 AND a.OwnerUserId = '##UserId##'), Delays AS (SELECT Id, CAST((JULIANDAY(ADate) - JULIANDAY(QDate)) * 1440.0 AS INT) AS Delay FROM Dates) SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN Delay <= 15 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS WITHin15, SUM(CASE WHEN Delay > 15 AND Delay <= 30 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS WITHin30, SUM(CASE WHEN Delay > 30 AND Delay <= 45 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS WITHin45, SUM(CASE WHEN Delay > 45 AND Delay <= 60 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS WITHinHour, SUM(CASE WHEN Delay > 60 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS MoreThanHour FROM Delays

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state with a colunm for each airport type sorted by state
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'heliport' THEN 1 END) AS heliport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'seaplane_base' THEN 1 END) AS seaplane_base_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'closed' THEN 1 END) AS closed_count
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

Very Buggy. Far from perfect. (Just for fun!) Max ~180 gifs
schema:
CREATE TABLE Posts (
    Id number,
    PostTypeId number,
    AcceptedAnswerId number,
    ParentId number,
    CreationDate time,
    DeletionDate time,
    Score number,
    ViewCount number,
    Body text,
    OwnerUserId number,
    OwnerDisplayName text,
    LastEditorUserId number,
    LastEditorDisplayName text,
    LastEditDate time,
    LastActivityDate time,
    Title text,
    Tags text,
    AnswerCount number,
    CommentCount number,
    FavoriteCount number,
    ClosedDate time,
    CommunityOwnedDate time,
    ContentLicense text
)
sql: SELECT SUBSTRING(Body, CHARINDEX(@stEnd, Body) + LEN(@stStart) - (CHARINDEX(REVERSE(@stStart), REVERSE(LEFT(Body, CHARINDEX(@stEnd, Body) + LEN(@stStart) - 1))) + LEN(@stStart) - 1), CHARINDEX(REVERSE(@stStart), REVERSE(LEFT(Body, CHARINDEX(@stEnd, Body) + LEN(@stStart) - 1))) + LEN(@stStart) - 1) AS "gif_url", CASE WHEN PostTypeId = 2 THEN 'Answer' ELSE 'Question' END AS "post_type", Id AS "post_link", CreationDate AS "post_date" FROM df WHERE CreationDate >= DATEADD(d, -30, GETDATE()) AND Body LIKE '%' + @stStart + '%' + @stEnd + '%' COLLATE SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS ORDER BY CreationDate DESC

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state with a colunm for each airport type and a column with an array of all  iata codes and names
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region,  
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport,  
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport,  
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport,  
       ARRAY_AGG(CONCAT_WS(' - ', iata_code, name)) AS iata_code_and_name  
FROM df  
WHERE iso_country = 'US'  
GROUP BY iso_region;

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped by state with a colunm for each airport type and a column with an array of all large airport iata codes sorted by state
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region AS state, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport_count, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport_count, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport_count, 
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'heliport' THEN 1 END) AS heliport_count, 
       ARRAY_AGG(iata_code ORDER BY iata_code) FILTER (WHERE type = 'large_airport') AS large_airport_iata_codes 
FROM df 
WHERE iso_country = 'US' 
GROUP BY iso_region;

query: Questions counted by time to first answer (w/o 24 hr restriction, log/log axis).
schema: CREATE TABLE df (Id number, PostTypeId number, AcceptedAnswerId number, ParentId number, CreationDate time, DeletionDate time, Score number, ViewCount number, Body text, OwnerUserId number, OwnerDisplayName text, LastEditorUserId number, LastEditorDisplayName text, LastEditDate time, LastActivityDate time, Title text, Tags text, AnswerCount number, CommentCount number, FavoriteCount number, ClosedDate time, CommunityOwnedDate time, ContentLicense text)
sql: SELECT LOG(10, CAST((JULIANDAY(CreationDate) - JULIANDAY(q.CreationDate)) * 1440.0 AS INT)) AS "Log Time (m)", LOG(10, COUNT(*)) FROM df AS q INNER JOIN df AS a ON a.ParentId = q.Id LEFT OUTER JOIN df AS a2 ON a.ParentId = a2.ParentId AND a.CreationDate > a2.CreationDate WHERE a2.Id IS NULL AND a.CreationDate >= q.CreationDate AND CAST((JULIANDAY(CreationDate) - JULIANDAY(q.CreationDate)) * 24.0 AS INT) > 24 AND CAST((JULIANDAY(CreationDate) - JULIANDAY(q.CreationDate)) * 1440.0 AS INT) > 0 GROUP BY CAST((JULIANDAY(CreationDate) - JULIANDAY(q.CreationDate)) * 1440.0 AS INT) ORDER BY CAST((JULIANDAY(CreationDate) - JULIANDAY(q.CreationDate)) * 1440.0 AS INT)

query: the aggreagated count of each type of airports in the US grouped and sorted by state one row per state with each type in its own column
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region as state,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) as large_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) as medium_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) as small_airport_count
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

query: Percent of closed answered negative-scored questions over time.
schema: CREATE TABLE Posts ( Id number, PostTypeId number, AcceptedAnswerId number, ParentId number, CreationDate time, DeletionDate time, Score number, ViewCount number, Body text, OwnerUserId number, OwnerDisplayName text, LastEditorUserId number, LastEditorDisplayName text, LastEditDate time, LastActivityDate time, Title text, Tags text, AnswerCount number, CommentCount number, FavoriteCount number, ClosedDate time, CommunityOwnedDate time, ContentLicense text )
sql: SELECT MAX(h.t), h.pc AS "Percent of closed answered negative-scored questions over time" FROM (SELECT q.t AS t, NTILE(100) OVER (ORDER BY q.t) AS pc FROM (SELECT ClosedDate - CreationDate AS t FROM df WHERE PostTypeId = 1 AND AnswerCount > 0 AND Score < 0 AND NOT ClosedDate IS NULL) AS q) AS h WHERE h.t <= '23:59:59' GROUP BY h.pc ORDER BY h.pc

query: Of questions that have upvoted answers, how many have accepted answers?.

sql: SELECT a.Id AS "Answer ID", p.Id AS "Question ID", p.Title AS "Title" FROM df AS p JOIN df AS a ON p.Id = a.ParentId WHERE p.PostTypeId = 1 AND a.OwnerUserId = '##UserId:int##' AND a.Score >= '##MinAnswerScore:int##' AND a.Id != p.AcceptedAnswerId

query: Questions by Time of Day and Day of Week. Designed to consider whether 'night' questions have more visibility than 'day' questions

sql: SELECT ((TIME_TO_STR(df.CreationDate, '%W')) + (TIME_TO_STR(df.CreationDate, '%h')) / 24.0) AS HourOfWeek, COUNT(df.Id) AS Questions FROM df WHERE PostTypeId = 1 GROUP BY TIME_TO_STR(df.CreationDate, '%W'), TIME_TO_STR(df.CreationDate, '%h') ORDER BY HourOfWeek

query: the aggregate count of each type  in the US grouped and sorted by state one row per state with each type in its own column
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region AS state,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'type1' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS type1_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'type2' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS type2_count
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

query: the count of each type of airport in the US grouped and sorted by state one row per state with each type in its own column
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region AS state,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS small_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS medium_airport_count,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS large_airport_count
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

query: Percentage of Users with 10K or 20K rep out of 'real users' (>100 rep).
schema: CREATE TABLE Users (Id number, Reputation number, CreationDate time, DisplayName text, LastAccessDate time, WebsiteUrl text, Location text, AboutMe text, Views number, UpVotes number, DownVotes number, ProfileImageUrl text, EmailHash text, AccountId number)
sql: SELECT (((SELECT CAST(COUNT(*) AS FLOAT) FROM df WHERE Reputation > 10000) / (SELECT CAST(COUNT(*) AS FLOAT) FROM df WHERE LastAccessDate > GETUTCDATE() - 30 AND Reputation > 200 AND (UpVotes + DownVotes) > 0)) * 100) AS PercentageOver10k, (((SELECT CAST(COUNT(*) AS FLOAT) FROM df WHERE Reputation > 20000) / (SELECT CAST(COUNT(*) AS FLOAT) FROM df WHERE LastAccessDate > GETUTCDATE() - 30 AND Reputation > 200 AND (UpVotes + DownVotes) > 0)) * 100) AS PercentageOver20k

query: the count of each type  in the US grouped and sorted by state one row per state with each type in its own column
schema: CREATE TABLE df (id INTEGER, ident VARCHAR, type VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, latitude_deg FLOAT, longitude_deg FLOAT, elevation_ft INTEGER, continent VARCHAR, iso_country VARCHAR, iso_region VARCHAR, municipality VARCHAR, scheduled_service VARCHAR, gps_code VARCHAR, iata_code VARCHAR, local_code VARCHAR, home_link VARCHAR, wikipedia_link VARCHAR, keywords VARCHAR);
sql:
SELECT iso_region, 
COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'Large_airport' THEN 1 END) AS Large_airport,
COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'Medium_airport' THEN 1 END) AS Medium_airport,
COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'Small_airport' THEN 1 END) AS Small_airport,
COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'Heliport' THEN 1 END) AS Heliport,
COUNT(CASE WHEN type = 'Seaplane_base' THEN 1 END) AS Seaplane_base
FROM df
WHERE iso_country = 'US'
GROUP BY iso_region
ORDER BY iso_region;

query: Avg Q & A' AVERAGE SCORES YEARLY comparison.
schema: CREATE TABLE df ( Id number, PostTypeId number, AcceptedAnswerId number, ParentId number, CreationDate time, DeletionDate time, Score number, ViewCount number, Body text, OwnerUserId number, OwnerDisplayName text, LastEditorUserId number, LastEditorDisplayName text, LastEditDate time, LastActivityDate time, Title text, Tags text, AnswerCount number, CommentCount number, FavoriteCount number, ClosedDate time, CommunityOwnedDate time, ContentLicense text )
sql: SELECT YEAR(CreationDate) AS "postyear", CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN PostTypeId = 1 THEN Score ELSE 0 END) AS FLOAT) / SUM(CASE WHEN PostTypeId = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS "q", CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN PostTypeId = 2 THEN Score ELSE 0 END) AS FLOAT) / SUM(CASE WHEN PostTypeId = 2 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS "a", CAST(SUM(Score) AS FLOAT) / SUM(1) AS "q&a" FROM df WHERE YEAR(CreationDate) >= 2008 AND ClosedDate IS NULL AND DeletionDate IS NULL AND CommunityOwnedDate IS NULL AND PostTypeId IN (1, 2) GROUP BY YEAR(CreationDate) ORDER BY YEAR(CreationDate)

query: the full state name and  average elevation translated from feet to meters of all large airports in the US grouped by state and sorted by elevation

SELECT iso_region AS full_state, AVG(elevation_ft * 0.3048) AS average_elevation

ORDER BY average_elevation;

query:
Good Question Without Good Answer: High Question / Top Answer Score Ratio. Divide the question score by the score of the top answer and sort in decreasing order.

Shows questions for which no good solution exist: most of those are either good feature requests or mathematical impossibilities.
schema:
CREATE TABLE Posts (
    Id number,
    PostTypeId number,
    AcceptedAnswerId number,
    ParentId number,
    CreationDate time,
    DeletionDate time,
    Score number,
    ViewCount number,
    Body text,
    OwnerUserId number,
    OwnerDisplayName text,
    LastEditorUserId number,
    LastEditorDisplayName text,
    LastEditDate time,
    LastActivityDate time,
    Title text,
    Tags text,
    AnswerCount number,
    CommentCount number,
    FavoriteCount number,
    ClosedDate time,
    CommunityOwnedDate time,
    ContentLicense text
)
sql: SELECT q.Id AS "post_link", q.Score AS "Question Score", MAX(a.Score) AS "Top Answer Score", CAST(q.Score AS FLOAT) / CAST(CASE WHEN MAX(a.Score) = 0 THEN 1 ELSE MAX(a.Score) END AS FLOAT) AS Ratio FROM df AS q INNER JOIN df AS a ON q.PostTypeId = 1 AND a.ParentId = q.Id GROUP BY q.Id, q.Score ORDER BY Ratio DESC LIMIT 100

sql: SELECT MIN("Bronze") FROM df WHERE "Total" = '3' AND "Silver" > '1' AND "Gold" < '1'
